# 📺 Trending YouTube Videos – EDA & Interactive Dashboard

This project performs a comprehensive **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)** on a dataset of trending YouTube videos. It uncovers powerful insights into viewer behavior, content popularity, and platform engagement patterns — all supported by beautiful **emoji-coded visualizations**, an **interactive Streamlit dashboard**, and a **PDF export report**.

![YouTube Banner](https://img.shields.io/badge/YouTube-Trending-blue?style=for-the-badge&logo=youtube)

---

## 📊 Key Features

- 🔥 Top 10 most viewed trending videos
- 📈 Correlation analysis of views, likes, comments, and dislikes
- 🏷️ Most commonly used tags (sampled for performance)
- 🌍 Country-wise average engagement (likes/views)
- ⏰ Heatmap showing popular trending hours and weekdays
- 📊 Category-based performance visualization
- 🖥️ Interactive **Streamlit dashboard** using Plotly
- 📄 Exportable PDF report using `matplotlib.backends.backend_pdf`
- 🎨 Emoji-coded titles for better storytelling and polish

---

## 🧰 Technologies Used

| Tool/Library     | Purpose                           |
|------------------|-----------------------------------|
| `Pandas`         | Data wrangling & cleaning         |
| `Matplotlib`     | Static plotting & PDF exporting   |
| `Seaborn`        | Statistical data visualizations   |
| `Plotly`         | Interactive charts (for dashboard)|
| `Streamlit`      | Real-time interactive dashboard   |
| `Jupyter`        | EDA and development notebook      |

